Two people died and a man is fighting for his life after a head-on collision on the N2 near Nonkcampa location outside King William’s Town in the morning. Tamara police opened a case of culpable homicide. The two vehicles, a silver BMW and a white KIA Sportage, collided in early hours. A man who sustained serious injuries was admitted to Grey Hospital, while two people died on the scene. The police have no information about the cause of the crash. Police spokeswoman captain Siphokazi Mawisa asked for anyone who witnessed the accident to come forward and call 040 659-7080. The accident comes just a day after the department of transport issued a rain warning urging motorists to be vigilant. Five people were killed in a head-on collision on the N2 between King William’s Town and Peddie on Sunday night. Two passengers were rushed to hospital. Four of the victims were believed to be hitch-hikers. Most of the dead or injured suffered severe head injuries. The two sedans collided 12km… October 6, 2015 In "News" EIGHT people died – five burnt beyond recognition – in a car crash outside Queenstown yesterday afternoon. The accident happened on the N6 at 2pm when a Toyota Avanza and Hyundai minibus collided head-on.Seven people were rushed to hospital. Two are in a critical condition, and the others are said… July 14, 2015 In "News" More than 20 people, including a soldier based in Grahamstown, lost their lives on roads across the province at the weekend. Scores more were injured, some critically. Yesterday provincial transport spokesman Ncedo Kumbaca said 22 people had been killed in 11 separate accidents between Friday and yesterday. He attributed the… May 9, 2016 In "News"